# cbc Life Management Platform
### Full-Stack: Node.js Backend + HTML/CSS/JS Frontend

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
cbc-app/
├── server.js          ← Express backend (API + auth)
├── package.json       ← Dependencies
├── data/
│   ├── users.json     ← User accounts (auto-created)
│   └── users/         ← Per-user data files (auto-created)
├── public/
│   └── index.html     ← Full frontend app
└── README.md
```

---

## 🚀 Quick Start

### 1. Install Node.js
Download from https://nodejs.org (v18 or higher)

### 2. Open the project in VS Code
```bash
cd cbc-app
code .
```

### 3. Install dependencies
Open the VS Code terminal (Ctrl+`) and run:
```bash
npm install
```

### 4. Start the server
```bash
npm start
```
You will see:
```
  ╔═══════════════════════════════════╗
  ║   cbc Life Platform — Backend     ║
  ║   Running on http://localhost:3000 ║
  ╚═══════════════════════════════════╝
```

### 5. Open in browser
Visit: **http://localhost:3000**

---

## 🔧 Development Mode (auto-restart)
```bash
npm run dev
```
Uses `nodemon` — server restarts automatically when you edit `server.js`.

---

## 🔑 Demo Account
A demo account is pre-registered when you first start the server:
- **Email:** demo@cbc.app
- **Password:** demo123

Or click **"Continue with Demo Account"** on the login screen.

---

## 🌐 API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | /api/auth/register | Create account |
| POST | /api/auth/login | Login → returns JWT |
| GET | /api/auth/me | Verify token |
| GET/PUT | /api/userdata | Bulk sync all data |
| GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | /api/tasks | Task management |
| GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | /api/habits | Habit tracking |
| GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | /api/nutrition/meals | Meal logging |
| GET/PUT | /api/nutrition/targets | Macro targets |
| GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | /api/exam/topics | Exam topics |
| GET/PUT | /api/exam/info | Exam settings |
| GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | /api/challenges | Challenges |
| GET/PUT | /api/planner | Daily planner |
| GET/PUT | /api/reflection | Daily reflection |
| GET/POST/DELETE | /api/focus/sessions | Focus sessions |
| GET/PUT | /api/focus/settings | Pomodoro settings |
| GET/PUT | /api/achievements/overrides | Manual unlock/lock |
| GET/POST/PUT/DELETE | /api/achievements/custom | Custom achievements |

All endpoints except `/api/auth/*` require:
```
Authorization: Bearer <your-jwt-token>
```

---

## 🔒 Security Notes
- Passwords are hashed with **bcrypt** (10 rounds)
- Authentication uses **JWT** tokens (30-day expiry)
- Change `JWT_SECRET` in `server.js` before deploying to production
- Data is stored in local JSON files — for production use MongoDB or PostgreSQL

---

## 🚀 Deploy to Production

### Render.com (Free)
1. Push this folder to a GitHub repo
2. Go to render.com → New Web Service
3. Connect your repo, set build command: `npm install`
4. Set start command: `npm start`
5. Deploy!

### Environment Variables (production)
```
PORT=3000
JWT_SECRET=your-very-long-random-secret-here
```

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack
- **Backend:** Node.js, Express, bcryptjs, jsonwebtoken
- **Frontend:** Pure HTML/CSS/JavaScript (no framework)
- **Database:** JSON files (file-based, no setup needed)
- **Charts:** Chart.js
- **Fonts:** Google Fonts (Syne + DM Mono)